        </How>

        <Summary>

            <p>
                In this article we learn't how to use aggregate functions on group of data using <Highlight>Count</Highlight>, <Highlight>Min</Highlight>, 
                <Highlight>Max</Highlight>, <Highlight>MinBy</Highlight>, <Highlight>MaxBy</Highlight>, <Highlight>Average</Highlight>, 
                <Highlight>Sum</Highlight> and <Highlight>Aggregate</Highlight>. LINQ aggregate functions are a valuable tool for working with collections of data in C#. 
                Whether you're counting items, finding the minimum or maximum value, computing the average or sum, or even performing custom aggregations, LINQ makes it simple and efficient to 
                perform these operations. All these can be used with any <Highlight>IEnumerable</Highlight> or <Highlight>IQueryable</Highlight> types.
            </p>
        </Summary>
